snippet: As talks over reopening routes in Pakistan drag on, they have become arguments over not just roads but money, drone strikes and, trickiest of all, intangible notions of honor and pride.
abstract: News analysis; talks over reopening NATO supply routes in Pakistan continue to drag on, becoming a haggle over not just money, but also over roads, drones strikes and intangible notions of honor and pride that play into electoral politics in both the United States and Pakistan.
lead_paragraph: As talks over reopening routes in Pakistan drag on, they have become arguments over not just roads but money, drone strikes and, trickiest of all, intangible notions of honor and pride.

headline.seo: U.S. and Pakistan in High-Stakes Haggle
headline.main: Notions of Honor Color High-Stakes Haggling Over NATO Supply Routes
